defaultthe first nine months of payment of housing benefits directly to tenants (available here:
default 
defaulthttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/direct-payment-demonstration-project-learning-and-payment-figures
default 
default).  Figures in the May press release show 6,168 tenants received direct payments, the total level of rent charged stood at £19,204,022 and an improvement in the average rent collection rate to 94%- with levels of payments by tenants on the projects varying from 91% to 97%. (This compares to an average of 92% published in a December 2012 press release covering the first four months).  The demonstration projects are being independently evaluated (funded by DWP) by a research consortium, from the Centre for Regional Economic and Social Research (CRESR) at
default 
defaultSheffield 
defaultHallam
default University, 
defaultthe Institute of Social Policy at the University of Oxford, and 
defaultlpsos
default MORI (IM). The evaluation findings, including full rent account analysis and the operation of switch-backs are due to be published in a series of reports in 2014.
